<br>
I know what I would choose.<br>
<br>
These changes appear to have begun to alter some of the problems of the warrior class.  Plus, they are a start to making the very high end game more challenging and fun.<br>
<br>
Also, it means that monks are less likely to be MTs, although I wish they had found a better way to do it.  The problem was not monk ac, the problem was the number of 0.1 weight all/all items.<br>
<br>
No mod rod2 and 7.5k CH increases the value of evasive/defensive warriors on raids.  If mana is no longer limitless, then it makes less sense to have knights or monks MT.  It may only be three minutes of glory, but it's a hell of a lot better than no glory at all.<br>
<br>
The MB nerf means we actually have a chance to do our Epic without amazing luck in beating the MB team to the kill or forking over a ton of cash to a pack of wizards.<br>
<br>
Yeah, there may be more nerfs out there, but so far, I'm not unhappy with what has happened.  VI seems to have some sort of long range plan and I'm hoping it works out.  I believe these changes will make the game more fun, once everyone has adjusted to them. <p>Hyardgune Varangian <BR> 58 Ogre Myrmidon of Gathered Might <BR> Solusek Ro</p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uhyardgune.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Hyardgune</A> at: 10/9/02 11:35:48 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=wychway>Wychway</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Formidable Opponent</span><br>  Posts: 180<br> <font color=#FF0000>(10/9/02 11:41:06 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthetavern.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1384.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Fix Warriors instead of nerfing encounters (along with m</span><hr size=1> We do not need the upgrade. The nerf coming is far superior for the longterm health of the game than buffing us now. <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=91801">Wychway Darkmink</a><BR>Inky Warlady, Bristlebane<BR><br>Facts:<br>1. Minks are mammals.<br> 
