<br>
Most people that say now it will take tactics are really just <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>   bored</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> with the tactics they have already learned.  The tactics would be setting up ch chain, mod rod chain, healers to heal the modding clerics, necros ready to twitch, bards available for mana song, <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>   tank switching</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->, etc...  To those that do this day in, day out they are bored with it.  To those (like my guild) just starting to learn these tactics they are still a challenge to us.<br>
<br>
These were all tactics that people have learned and are still learning, but now are thrown out the window for what <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>   new</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> tactics required for a shorter fight?  There has been yet one concrete example on any new tactics.  If one person could give one good example of a tactic change due to this patch, we would all be interested.<br>
<br>
If mobs have lower HP, and you have lowered abilities to keeping a single tank or chain of tanks alive indefinitely, so you have to make up for it in raw dps.  All that means is more people, for more damage, i.e. the zerg everyone complains about.  If <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  anything</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> the guilds that do zerg and supposedly dont have good tactics will quickly rise on the power curve since they can throw raw numbers at a mob.  In fights today where people scoff at those that loose a fight when they have 80 people since they can do it in 35, you are gonna be in for a rude surprise.<br>
<br>
If you try to do it with same number / class ratio you do today, you may find your self in continually loosing battles or long recoveries from fights.  Class ratios may need to be changed or people asked to play their alts more often.  Neither scenario sounds like much fun.<br>
<br>
Many more <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>   interesting</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> things could have been done in PoP to and force people to use new strategies.  Creative ae effects, creative mob abilities, creative zones, fixed pathing, better mob ai, etc.. could have all nullified the tactics above and left well enough alone in the previous expansions.  In fact it seems like more work, more hassle and more bad pr to redo all this stuff instead of just making it work right in PoP. <p><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=94501>Viiperan Deepfang</a><BR>
