<br>
we have built our guilds in such a way as to be able to raid a certain class of mob. this hypothetical retuning might open the door to people who never had the organization or the classes to make a viable attempt. significantly more competition for boss mobs = unhappy guild.<br>
<br>
smaller guilds who have built a strategy that enables them to do significant mobs because of a great cleric rotation and near infinite mana will be challenged to recruit more heavily, perhaps changing their guild forever.<br>
<br>
BUT like everything else change is good at shaking up all of us who have become complacent and think we have all the answers. from that aspect alone, i look forward to the changes.<br>
<br>
As a MT, I do feel that the approach to melee balancing taken by VI at this juncture is grossly incomplete. Monks will now get hit less often but for more pts (see monkly business new section). I have not seen anything that addresses warrior issues regarding defense and offensive short comings. We probably never will. The PoP AA stuff seems more of the same, 1 or 2 great, handful of nice and rest crap. <br>
<br>
frankly, i usually dont bitch or concern myself with this stuff but when VI comes out and plans do do something significant without addressing the issue broadly, i am disappointed. In any event, i look forward to seeing what the changes actually bring and how they will affect boss mob fights and the competition for those fights. <br>
